European Benchmark Coal Declines to Lowest Price in a Week

-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 
2011-10-13T10:44:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/european-benchmark-coal-declines-to-lowest-price-in-a-week.html
Benchmark European coal declined to
its lowest price in more than a week.  Thermal coal for 2012 delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or
Antwerp decreased as much as 1.9 percent to $118.50 a metric
ton, its lowest level since Oct. 5, and was at $118.85 at 11:30
a.m. in  London , according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Bloomberg tracks data from information supplied by ICAP
Plc, GFI Group Inc., Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group
AG, IHS McCloskey, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  